From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: forkd v0.3 <noreply@deeplethe.com>
Date: 2026-05-18
Subject: [PATCH] Add MemoryBackend::Memfd for forkd live-branching

Adds a third MemoryBackend variant beside File and Uffd: Memfd.
When set, Firecracker connects to the UDS, RECEIVES a memfd over
SCM_RIGHTS from the handler, and mmaps it MAP_PRIVATE as guest
RAM. Multiple Firecracker processes pointing at the same memfd
get kernel-CoW page sharing (one physical page per clean address
across N children), which is the property forkd's fan-out
primitive needs.

Pairs with forkd's userfaultfd handler crate (separate repo);
the handler creates the memfd, listens on the UDS, and on
firecracker connect sends back the memfd fd. forkd's daemon
sequences this so source-VM start and children's restore both
use the same memfd, with uffd_wp on top to handle source writes
without invalidating children's view.

Applies cleanly to firecracker tag v1.10.1.

NOT YET TESTED — this is a starting-point patch produced from
reading the v1.10.1 source. Verification on the dev box is the
next step.

